author: kfogel
msg: Resolve issue #2096: We were temporarily #defining MIN, and then
#undefining it when done.  But some systems define MIN themselves, and
not only did our definition replace theirs (not a big deal, since ours
almost certainly did exactly the same thing as the system's), when we
later undefined it, we effectively removed both definitions.  Oops.
Solution: use a different name.
* subversion/libsvn_delta/compose_delta.c
(copy_source_ops): Use TMP_MIN instead of MIN, to avoid overlap with
a possible system-defined MIN.

author: kfogel
msg: Follow up to r11396: Make the version header translatable again.
Suggested by: Erik Hülsmann <e.huelsmann@gmx.net>
While at it, clean up the code a bit.
* subversion/clients/cmdline/cl.h
(svn_cl__help_header, svn_cl__help_footer): Remove extern
declarations of these.  They live in one C file, and are passed as
parameters from there to where they are used, so there is no need
for the names to be exported.
* subversion/clients/cmdline/help-cmd.c
(svn_cl__help_header, svn_cl__help_footer): Remove these...
(print_help): ...replacing them with local variables here.
Interpolate SVN_VER_NUMBER using apr_psprintf instead of
preprocessor concatenation, so gettext will still work.
